#. <section class="sutta" id="sn56.47"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn56.47:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 56"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 56"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn56.47:0.2"
msgid "5. Papātavagga"
msgstr "5. A Cliff"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 47. Paṭhamachiggaḷayugasutta → chiggalasuttaṃ (bj) | chiggaḷa 2 (pts1)
msgctxt "sn56.47:0.3"
msgid "47. Paṭhamachiggaḷayugasutta"
msgstr "47. A Yoke With a Hole (1st)"

# BB has “blind”, but the standard meaning of kana is one-eyed, and there seems no reason why not here.
#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi5.456"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
#. VAR: ekacchiggaḷaṃ → ekacchiggalaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn56.47:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso mahāsamudde ekacchiggaḷaṃ yugaṃ pakkhipeyya. "
"Tatrāpissa kāṇo kacchapo. So vassasatassa vassasatassa accayena sakiṃ sakiṃ "
"ummujjeyya."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, suppose a person was to throw a yoke with a single hole into "
"the ocean. And there was a one-eyed turtle who popped up once every hundred "
"years."

msgctxt "sn56.47:1.2"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn56.47:1.3"
msgid ""
"api nu kho kāṇo kacchapo vassasatassa vassasatassa accayena sakiṃ sakiṃ "
"ummujjanto amusmiṃ ekacchiggaḷe yuge gīvaṃ paveseyyā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Would that one-eyed turtle, popping up once every hundred years, still poke "
"its neck through the hole in that yoke?”"

msgctxt "sn56.47:1.4"
msgid "“Yadi nūna, bhante, kadāci karahaci dīghassa addhuno accayenā”ti."
msgstr "“Only after a very long time, sir, if ever.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: vinipātagatena bālena → vinipātaṃ gatena bālena (si) | vinītagatena bahulena (mr)
msgctxt "sn56.47:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Khippataraṃ kho so, bhikkhave, kāṇo kacchapo vassasatassa vassasatassa "
"accayena sakiṃ sakiṃ ummujjanto amusmiṃ ekacchiggaḷe yuge gīvaṃ paveseyya, "
"na tvevāhaṃ, bhikkhave, sakiṃ vinipātagatena bālena manussattaṃ vadāmi."
msgstr ""
"“That one-eyed turtle would poke its neck through the hole in that yoke "
"sooner than a fool who has fallen to the underworld would be reborn as a "
"human being, I say."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.47:3.1"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn56.47:3.2"
msgid ""
"Na hettha, bhikkhave, atthi dhammacariyā, samacariyā, kusalakiriyā, "
"puññakiriyā."
msgstr ""
"Because there there’s no principled or moral conduct, and no doing what is "
"good and skillful."

msgctxt "sn56.47:3.3"
msgid "Aññamaññakhādikā ettha, bhikkhave, vattati dubbalakhādikā."
msgstr "There they just prey on each other, preying on the weak."

msgctxt "sn56.47:3.4"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu?"
msgstr "Why is that?"

msgctxt "sn56.47:3.5"
msgid "Adiṭṭhattā, bhikkhave, catunnaṃ ariyasaccānaṃ."
msgstr "It’s because they haven’t seen the four noble truths."

msgctxt "sn56.47:3.6"
msgid "Katamesaṃ catunnaṃ?"
msgstr "What four?"

msgctxt "sn56.47:3.7"
msgid ""
"Dukkhassa ariyasaccassa … pe … dukkhanirodhagāminiyā paṭipadāya "
"ariyasaccassa."
msgstr "The noble truths of suffering, its origin, its cessation, and the path."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn56.47:4.1"
msgid ""
"Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yogo karaṇīyo … pe … ‘ayaṃ "
"dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yogo karaṇīyo”ti."
msgstr "That’s why you should practice meditation …”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn56.47:4.2"
msgid "Sattamaṃ."
msgstr ""
